
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 07 of Thoracic MRT
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Scapular mass' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I know' radio button

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'T1w Signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w Signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Cystic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Septated/chambered' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fluid level' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Nidus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fat signal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sclerosis' checkbox is enabled

And 'Periosteal reaction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cartilage cap' checkbox is enabled
And 'Signal-poor perichondrium, covering cartilage cap' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sclerotic margin' checkbox is enabled

And 'Expansile' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteolytic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteoblastic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Permeative growth' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sclerotic margin' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pedunculated, growing away from epiphysis growing away from epiphysis' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Calcification' checkbox
Then 'Central' checkbox is enabled
And 'Diffusely distributed' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Nidus' checkbox
Then 'T2w hyperintense' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Cartilage cap' checkbox
Then 'Max. thickness' input field is enabled
And 'T2w hyperintense' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Sclerotic margin' checkbox
Then 'Map-like' checkbox is enabled
